Pang
</taxonomicName>
et
</emphasis>
Ś 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[482,521,151,176]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">lipi</emphasis>
ń 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[537,667,151,176]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">ski sp. nov.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[683,774,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[151,1409,350,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,339,1946]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 24. Epilachna crepida. (a, b) Dorsal view; (c) lateral view; (d) anterior view; (e) postcoxal line; (f) tegmen inner; (g) tegmen lateral; (h) paramere; (i) apical sclerite of penis; (j) penis" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3924042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3924042/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Figs. 
<number box="[746,774,151,175]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
a–j)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1435,223,284]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,272,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name is derived from the Latin noun 
<emphasis box="[842,933,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName box="[842,929,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Epilachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crepida">crepida</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
meaning shoe, sandal or boot and refers to a shoe-like apical piece of penis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3924042" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3924042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3924042/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" targetBox="[151,1409,350,1908]" targetPageId="29">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1969,2023]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,288,1969,1992]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">FIGURE 24.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[293,480,1970,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Epilachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crepida">
<emphasis box="[293,480,1970,1992]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Epilachna 
<taxonomicName box="[404,480,1970,1992]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="species" species="crepida">crepida</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (a, b) Dorsal view; (c) lateral view; (d) anterior view; (e) postcoxal line; (f) tegmen inner; (g) tegmen lateral; (h) paramere; (i) apical sclerite of penis; (j) penis
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This species can be easily distinguished by its male genitalia, particularly by its complex form of penis guide and shoe-like apical part of the penis (
<figureCitation box="[714,806,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[151,1409,350,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,339,1946]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 24. Epilachna crepida. (a, b) Dorsal view; (c) lateral view; (d) anterior view; (e) postcoxal line; (f) tegmen inner; (g) tegmen lateral; (h) paramere; (i) apical sclerite of penis; (j) penis" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3924042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3924042/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Figs. 
<number box="[777,806,188,212]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
f–j).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Description</emphasis>
. Length 
<quantity box="[432,521,223,247]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.3" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="7.3">7.3 mm</quantity>
. TL/EW = 
<number box="[646,698,223,247]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1.3">1.30</number>
; PL/PW = 
<number box="[820,873,223,247]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="0.35">0.35</number>
; EL/EW = 
<number box="[998,1049,223,247]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1.11">1.11</number>
; EL/PL = 
<number box="[1164,1217,223,247]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="5.64">5.64</number>
. Dorsum reddish or reddish brown; pronotum with central transverse spot of varying size. Elytra with 
<number box="[1081,1095,260,284]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="5.0">5</number>
pairs of black spots, arranged as on 
<figureCitation box="[219,300,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[151,1409,350,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,339,1946]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 24. Epilachna crepida. (a, b) Dorsal view; (c) lateral view; (d) anterior view; (e) postcoxal line; (f) tegmen inner; (g) tegmen lateral; (h) paramere; (i) apical sclerite of penis; (j) penis" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3924042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3924042/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Fig. 
<number box="[271,300,295,319]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
a–d; anterior and posterior spots separated from margins and suture; spots three and four sometimes connected and reaching lateral margin of elytron. Abdominal postcoxal line incomplete, extending posteriorly to 
<number box="[151,186,367,391]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="0.8">0.8</number>
of ventrite length (
<figureCitation box="[400,477,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[173,1373,157,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[166,1410,157,1933]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 23. Epilachna bocaki. (a) Dorsal view; (b) anterior view; (c) lateral view; (d) female genitalia; (e) postcoxal line; (f) tegmen inner; (g) tegmen lateral; (h) paramere; (i) penis; (j) apical sclerite of penis" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3924040" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3924040/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Fig 
<number box="[446,477,367,391]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
e).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,371,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[391,487,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[151,1409,350,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,339,1946]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 24. Epilachna crepida. (a, b) Dorsal view; (c) lateral view; (d) anterior view; (e) postcoxal line; (f) tegmen inner; (g) tegmen lateral; (h) paramere; (i) apical sclerite of penis; (j) penis" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3924042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3924042/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Figs. 
<number box="[459,487,404,428]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
f–j): penis weakly bent basally, with shoe-like apical piece; parameres distinctly longer than penis guide; penis guide very complex, with single apical hook. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1004,1209,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Female genitalia:</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
